'''Haris Tabaković''' ({{IPA|bs|xâːris tǎbakoʋitɕ|pron}}; born 20 June 1994) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], on loan from [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]]. Born in Switzerland, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Tabaković started his professional career at [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]], who loaned him to [[FC Wil|Wil]] in 2014. Two years later, he joined [[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshoppers]]. The following year, he moved to [[Debreceni VSC|Debrecen]]. In 2019, he switched to [[Diósgyőri VTK|Diósgyőr]]. Tabaković signed with [[SC Austria Lustenau|Austria Lustenau]] in 2020. In 2022, he joined [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]]. A year later, he was transferred to [[Hertha BSC]]. The following year, he moved to TSG Hoffenheim, who sent him on loan to Borussia Mönchengladbach the following year.

A former Swiss youth international, Tabaković made his senior international debut for Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2023, earning 10 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Tabaković came through the youth academy of [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]. He made his professional debut against [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] on 7 October 2012 at the age of 18. On 14 September 2013, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[SC Young Fellows Juventus|Young Fellows Juventus]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/28712-mladi-napadac-haris-tabakovic-zabio-prvi-gol-za-young-boyse|title=Mladi napadač Haris Tabaković zabio prvi gol za Young Boyse|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=15 September 2013|access-date=15 September 2013|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2014, he was sent on a 18-month loan to [[FC Wil|Wil]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/young-boys-tabakovica-posudio-wilu/121792|title=Young Boys Tabakovića posudio Wilu|website=sportsport.ba|date=7 January 2014|access-date=10 January 2014|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2016, he joined [[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshoppers]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/haris-tabakovic-novi-igrac-grasshoppersa/236803|title=Haris Tabaković novi igrač Grasshoppersa|website=sportsport.ba|date=13 January 2016|access-date=15 January 2016|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2017, Tabaković signed with Hungarian team [[Debreceni VSC|Debrecen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo-nb-i/2017/08/dvsc-alairt-a-svajci-bosnyak-kozepcsatar|title=DVSC: Aláírt a Svájci-Bosnyák Középcsatár|website=nemzetisport.hu|date=2 August 2017|access-date=3 August 2017|language=hu}}</ref>

In June 2019, he switched to [[Diósgyőri VTK|Diósgyőr]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo-nb-i/2019/06/dvtk-egy-uj-igazolas-debrecenbol-es-nyolc-edzomeccs|title=DVTK: Új igazolás Debrecenből és nyolc edzőmeccs|website=nemzetisport.hu|date=5 June 2019|access-date=5 June 2019|language=hu}}</ref>

In September 2020, he joined Austrian side [[SC Austria Lustenau|Austria Lustenau]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://laola1.at/de/fussball/2-liga/news/austria-lustenau-verpflichtet-haris-tabakovic|title=Austria Lustenau verpflichtet Haris Tabakovic|website=laola1.at|date=14 September 2020|access-date=15 September 2020|language=de}}</ref> He scored his first career [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] against [[SV Lafnitz|Lafnitz]] on 23 May 2021.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://laola1.at/de/fussball/2-liga/news/kroepfl-und-tabakovic-bei-4-4-mit-triplepack|title=Kröpfl und Tabakovic bei 4:4 mit Triplepack|website=laola1.at|date=23 May 2021|access-date=25 May 2021|language=de}}</ref>

In March 2022, he moved to [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kurier.at/sport/fussball/austria-verpflichtete-zweitliga-torjaeger-tabakovic-von-lustenau/401949703|title=Austria verpflichtete Zweitliga-Torjäger Tabakovic von Lustenau|website=kurier.at|date=24 March 2022|access-date=25 March 2022|language=de}}</ref>

===Hertha BSC===
In August 2023, Tabaković signed a three-year deal with German outfit [[Hertha BSC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/tabakovic-potpisao-naredne-sezone-u-herthi-cemo-gledati-bh-napadacki-tandem/2686284|title=Tabaković potpisao: Naredne sezone u Herthi ćemo gledati bh. napadački tandem|website=fokus.ba|date=1 August 2023|access-date=1 August 2023|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the team on 4 August against [[SV Wehen Wiesbaden|Wehen Wiesbaden]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/prevljak-i-tabakovic-upisali-zvanicni-debi-hertha-porazena-na-domacem-terenu|title=Prevljak i Tabaković upisali zvanični debi, Hertha poražena na domaćem terenu|website=scsport.ba|date=4 August 2023|access-date=6 August 2023|language=bs}}</ref> On 12 August, he scored his first goal for Hertha BSC in a [[2023–24 DFB-Pokal#First round|DFB-Pokal]] game against [[FC Carl Zeiss Jena|Carl Zeiss Jena]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/potencijalni-reprezentativac-bih-je-kralj-sesnaesterca-pogledajte-kako-je-tabakovic-postigao-gol-za-herthu|title=Potencijalni reprezentativac BiH je kralj šesnaesterca: Pogledajte kako je Tabaković postigao gol za Herthu|website=sportske.ba|date=12 August 2023|access-date=15 August 2023|language=bs}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored a brace in a defeat of [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]], which were his first league goals for the squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/vijesti-koje-raduju-kodru-prevljak-briljirao-sa-golom-i-asistencijom|title=Vijesti koje raduju Kodru: Prevljak briljirao sa golom i asistencijom|website=n1info.ba|date=26 August 2023|access-date=27 August 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

Tabaković scored his first hat-trick for the club in a victory over [[Eintracht Braunschweig]] on 17 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/haris-tabakovic-je-prava-gol-masina-potencijalni-zmaj-postigao-hat-trick-za-33-minute/230917075|title=Haris Tabaković je prava gol-mašina: Potencijalni Zmaj postigao hat-trick za 33 minute|website=klix.ba|date=17 September 2023|access-date=20 September 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

With 22 goals, he finished the [[2023–24 2. Bundesliga|2023–24]] season as [[List of 2. Bundesliga top scorers|2. Bundesliga top scorer]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://raport.ba/tabakovic-dobio-priznanje-za-najboljeg-strijelca-2-bundeslige-njemacke|title=Tabaković dobio priznanje za najboljeg strijelca 2. Bundeslige Njemačke|website=raport.ba|date=20 May 2024|access-date=20 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

===TSG Hoffenheim===
In August, Tabaković was transferred to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/haris-tabakovic-potpisao-za-hoffenheim|title=Haris Tabaković potpisao za Hoffenhiem|website=n1info.ba|date=23 August 2024|access-date=25 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the side against [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on 31 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/bundesliga-demirovic-usao-s-klupe-tabakovic-i-gigovic-upisali-debitantske-nastupe|title=Bundesliga: Demirović ušao s klupe, Tabaković i Gigović upisali debitantske nastupe|website=sportske.ba|date=31 August 2024|access-date=1 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref> On 19 October, he scored his first goal for TSG Hoffenheim in a win over [[VfL Bochum]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/443633-haris-tabakovic-postigao-prvi-gol-za-hoffenheim|title=Haris Tabaković postigao prvi gol za Hoffenheim|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=19 October 2024|access-date=20 October 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In July 2025, he was loaned to [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/986337/haris-tabakovic-u-borussiji-monchengladbach|title=Haris Tabaković u Borussiji Mönchengladbach|website=avaz.ba|date=19 July 2025|access-date=20 July 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Despite representing [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] at various youth levels, Tabaković decided to play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at the senior level.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/405956-tabakovic-ce-uskoro-zaigrati-za-bih-ostalo-je-jos-nekoliko-stvari-da-se-rijesi|title=Tabaković će uskoro zaigrati za BiH: Ostalo je još nekoliko stvari da se riješi|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=19 October 2023|access-date=20 October 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

In November 2023, his request to change sports citizenship from Swiss to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/odlicne-vijesti-haris-tabakovic-dobio-pravo-nastupa-za-bosnu-i-hercegovinu/462174|title=Odlične vijesti: Haris Tabaković dobio pravo nastupa za Bosnu i Hercegovinu|website=sportsport.ba|date=7 November 2023|access-date=10 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref> Earlier that month, he received his first senior call up, for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group J|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] and [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/savo-milosevic-objavio-spisak-zmajeva-nekoliko-novih-imena-na-njemu|title=Savo Milošević objavio spisak Zmajeva, nekoliko novih imena na njemu|website=n1info.ba|date=2 November 2023|access-date=5 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 16 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/generacijska-sramota-tragikomicni-zmajevi-nastavili-brukati-drzavni-dres/172326|title=Generacijska sramota: Tragikomični Zmajevi nastavili brukati državni dres|website=faktor.ba|date=16 November 2023|access-date=18 November 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

On 12 October, in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Malta national football team|Malta]], he scored his first senior international goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/foto-cetiri-razlicita-strijelca-za-pobjedu-protiv-malte-zmajevi-odlicni-u-prijateljskoj-utakmici-1082635|title=Četiri različita strijelca za pobjedu protiv Malte: Zmajevi odlični u prijateljskoj utakmici|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=12 October 2025|access-date=12 October 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Tabaković was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Tabaković married his long-time girlfriend Sabrina in June 2024.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/haris-tabakovic-ozenio-njemacku-manekenku-otkrila-ih-njena-objava-na-instagramu/240622059|title=Haris Tabaković oženio njemačku manekenku, otkrila ih njena objava na Instagramu|website=klix.ba|date=22 June 2024|access-date=24 June 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Ermedin Demirović]], [[Jusuf Gazibegović]], [[Nihad Mujakić]], [[Haris Hajradinović]], [[Dženis Burnić]], [[Sead Kolašinac]], [[Enver Kulašin]], [[Nail Omerović]], [[Benjamin Tahirović]], [[Osman Hadžikić]] and [[Ermin Bičakčić]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Ilidža]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/prvo-dzuma-a-onda-put-za-zenicu-bh-reprezentativci-iznenadili-prisutne-u-dzamiji-na-ilidzi/483813|title=Prvo džuma, a onda put za Zenicu: Bh. reprezentativci iznenadili prisutne u džamiji na Ilidži|website=sportsport.ba|date=11 October 2024|access-date=12 October 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

